version_description: Acoustic version based on acoustic performance by D at Sea.
Because my version is easier with easier chord. for people who are learning to play the guitar.
Main difference is the bassline, that is now present. Also, the chords are more advanced.
More accurate to the studio version, developed on piano so some chords may not work perfectly when played on guitar.
This is the first version on ultimate guitar so any ideas of improvement are welcome :).
More detailed version with better position of chords
Mine is simpler for beginners and much easier to play, but still sounds awesome :)
Specific, corrected chords true to capo, labeled and timed sections, timing and layering cues, strumming patterns.

song_name: I Thought I Knew What Love Was

version_description: 2 sets of chord shapes are included in this tab... you can choose to either capo the 6th fret and play chords in the key of C, or tune down 1/2 step and play chords in key of G... From the official music video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K1-TbFsJwnY.
